articles.title: Paris Paralympics open in blaze of hope and inclusivity
articles.description: Paralympics opened in Paris on Wednesday in a colourful and hope-filled ceremony, starting 11 days of competition in a city still riding the wave of the successful Olympics.  French President Emmanuel Macron declared the Games open during a ceremony in a balmy Place de la Concorde in central Paris—the first time a Paralympic opening ceremony has taken place away from the main stadium.
